headline: Oil Rallies on Trump Sanctions. Traders See a Head-Fake.
summary: Oil prices were rallying Thursday after President Donald Trump imposed sanctions on Russian producers Rosneft and Lukoil.  Brent  crude futures, the international benchmark, rose 5.9% to $66.29 a barrel.  West Texas Intermediate (  WTI  ) was up 6.3% to $62.17 a barrel, its largest gain since June.

headline: Do Analyst Updates and Portfolio Shifts Foreshadow a New Chapter for EOG Resources (EOG)?
summary: Several brokerage firms have recently updated their research on EOG Resources, maintaining neutral to positive ratings while revising key assumptions prior to the company's third-quarter earnings announcement. An institutional investor, Northside Capital Management, has reduced its EOG Resources holdings by around 30% as part of a broader adjustment in its energy sector exposure, reflecting ongoing portfolio rebalancing trends among large funds. headline: EOG Resources Earnings Preview: What to Expect
summary: Energy sector giant EOG Resources is gearing up to announce its Q3 results by early November, and analysts expect a notable double-digit drop in earnings.
